sentences: Charles Delaunay (18 January 1911 – 16 February 1988) was a French author, jazz expert, co-founder and long-term leader of the Hot Club de France.
In 1935, together with Panassié he founded Le Jazz Hot, one of the oldest jazz magazines.
From 1937, Delaunay shared artists and repertory responsibilities with Panassié on a new record label, Disques Swing ("Swing Records").
Jazz hot ceased publication in summer 1939, being revived in March 1945.
Jazz hot ceased publication in summer 1939, being revived in March 1945.
In 1948, Delaunay founded the record label Disques Vogue and was one of the first people to introduce bop into France, but Panassié did not even consider the new music to be jazz.
Delaunay died in Paris of Parkinson's disease in 1988.
